# XMT BRD Authoring Standards

## Requirement IDs

Every business rule **must** have a unique ID using the format `BR-{MODULE}-{NNN}`:

| Module | Prefix |
|--------|--------|
| Subscription / Tenancy | `BR-SUB` |
| Pro Forma Invoice | `BR-PFI` |
| Invoice | `BR-INV` |
| Credit Note | `BR-CN` |
| Debit Note | `BR-DN` |
| Refund Note | `BR-RN` |
| Payment Received | `BR-PAY` |
| Journal Entry | `BR-JNL` |
| Shared / Cross-module | `BR-SHR` |

Example:
```
**BR-INV-001** When an invoice is saved with status `Draft`, the invoice number must be generated using `thisapp.invoice.generateNumber`.
```

## Confidence Tags

Every requirement must end with a confidence tag on the same line:

- `[Confirmed]` ‚Äî behavior verified directly in Deluge code
- `[Inferred]` ‚Äî behavior strongly implied by code structure but not explicitly traced
- `[Open Question]` ‚Äî behavior unknown or ambiguous; must also be logged in ¬ß9

‚ùå Do not state requirements as fact if you cannot trace them to code.
‚úÖ Mark them `[Inferred]` or `[Open Question]` instead.

## Rule Writing Template

Use imperative, single-responsibility sentences:

```
**BR-{MODULE}-{NNN}** When [trigger/condition], system must [behavior][, unless [exception]]. [Confidence]
```

Avoid:
- Vague phrasing: "handles", "manages", "deals with"
- Passive voice: "is generated", "will be set"
- Bundling multiple rules into one sentence

## Module Section Template

Every module in ¬ß5 must follow this exact structure (do not skip subsections):

```markdown
### 5.X Module Name

#### Purpose
One paragraph: what this module represents and its role in the billing chain.

#### When and How It Is Created
Describe creation triggers: manual form, workflow, schedule, conversion from another document.

#### Business Rules and Validations
List each rule with ID, requirement sentence, and confidence tag.

#### Calculations
Line total, tax, balance impact formulas with field name references.

#### Relationships to Other Modules
Upstream (what creates this) and downstream (what this feeds into).

#### Status Lifecycle
List all statuses and valid transitions. Reference the Blueprint name if applicable.

#### Implementation Status
`Done` | `Partial` | `Not Started` ‚Äî with one-line note on gaps if Partial.
```

## Synchronization Requirements

After completing any module:
1. Update the corresponding row in **¬ß8 Implementation Status Matrix**
2. Log any `[Open Question]` items in **¬ß9 Open Questions**
3. Update **¬ß6 Document Conversion Matrix** if the module converts to/from other documents

## Reference Module

**¬ß5.3 Invoice is the canonical reference module.** Write it first and in full. All other modules must match its depth and tone.
